            <head type="main-derived">Arms were very different from now</head>
            
            <ab>Arms were very different from now.  The <del rend="overstrike">ponderous</del> carbine, <add place="supralinear" rend="insertion">the <del rend="overstrike">gun</del> infantry guns of</add>
                of those days <del rend="overstrike">had to be</del> was ponderous and slow, and would now be looked upon with derision.&#8212;The pike was a stout heavy iron&#8209;pointed weapon, of ash,
                twelve to sixteen feet long&#8212;the <del rend="overstrike">equip</del> personal equipment of the soldiers was <!-- [TJ] Is 'a' in 'was' over an 'e' as if he were to write 'were'? --> also <del rend="overstrike">very</del> cumbrous&#8212;the halberd was a battle
                &#8209;axe fastened to a long pole&#8212;
            </ab>
            
